  </sponsors>
  <source>Bayer</source>
  <oversight_info>
    <is_fda_regulated_drug>No</is_fda_regulated_drug>
    <is_fda_regulated_device>No</is_fda_regulated_device>
  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The main objective of this project is to evaluate savings in direct costs as regards the use
      of rivaroxaban versus vitamin K antagonists (VKAs) in routine clinical practice using data
      from three cohorts of patients receiving VKAs or rivaroxaban in Spain, including the time in
      therapeutic range (TTR) values of the same and the incidence of events in the first year
      following diagnosis.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
